unittitle_ssm: Records of the Hall of Fame for Great Americans
abstract_ssm: New York University established the Hall of Fame for Great Americans in 1900 as a part of the library structure at their former University Heights campus. As the first ever hall of fame in the United States, it was created to honor great men and women who have had a significant impact on the nation's history. Spanning the period 1901-1985, the Records of the Hall of Fame for Great Americans documents the history of the hall of fame, from its founding through the sale of the University Heights campus to the City University of New York in 1973. The collection includes programs from many, but not all, of the bust unveiling ceremonies as well as general correspondence, administrative files, newspaper clippings, and a selection of published books.
